<h1 class="page-title">Books</h1>

<div class="books-intro">
  <p>Below is a list of books that have travelled en route with me over the last three years, and the list keeps growing.</p>
  <p>Sharing the quote from a random magazine I spotted in a little bookshop in Hong Kong but stays with me firmly:</p>
  <blockquote>
    <p>"The trouble with ebooks is that no one else can see what you're reading. Like it or not, books are an astonishingly efficient accessory."</p>
    <p>"To love a book is to be overcome by an innate desire to advertise it, so that others might read it and love it too. When there's a book we've enjoyed but can't keep, and we leave it on the communal wall, and then we come back later and it's gone, it's fulfilling in a shimmeringly complex way. Someone else might be reading it: someone else's mind might be becoming just that little bit more connected to our own."</p>
  </blockquote>
</div>

{% for book in collections.books | reverse %}
<article class="book">
  <a class="book-cover-link" href="{{ book.data.amazon }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
    <img class="book-cover" src="{{ book.data.cover }}" alt="{{ book.data.title }}" loading="lazy">
  </a>
  <h2 class="book-title"><a href="{{ book.data.amazon }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">{{ book.data.title }}</a></h2>
  <time class="entry-date" datetime="{{ book.date | isoDate }}">{{ book.date | readableDate }}</time>
  <div class="book-review">{{ book.templateContent | safe }}</div>
</article>
{% endfor %}
